strength of this country has been at the academic

26:00.850 --> 26:16.068
institutions, at the universities. And I think 
this is the reason that the country leads the world

26:16.088 --> 26:24.158
in oceanography, because of the academic 
atmosphere. and the impact of the students on

26:24.779 --> 26:32.386
their professors in tackling various problems 
and in keeping them sharpened up. And so I get

26:32.606 --> 26:45.278
concerned when we talk about giving 
responsibility for supporting research to an

26:32.606 --> 26:45.278
agency with an in-house capability. And I'm going 
to do whatever I can to make sure at the basic

26:52.927 --> 27:15.810
research component, the research component of 
the country stays that the university is

26:52.927 --> 27:15.810
supported through grants and contracts from 
whatever source, and that that pot of money is

26:52.927 --> 27:15.810
protected very carefully by the federal 
government, from inroads, by in-house

26:52.927 --> 27:15.810
laboratories. And I have a strong conviction from 
my days at ONR and watching the Air Force turn the

27:20.737 --> 27:36.537
responsibility for their basic research in 
geophysics over to the geophysics research

27:20.737 --> 27:36.537
directorate, which was a laboratory up in 
Massachusetts, and then watching their contract

27:20.737 --> 27:36.537
research program disappear. It's very easy to 
say, well, I need a million dollars because I've

27:37.318 --> 27:45.127
got a laboratory with a whole bunch of civil 
servants in it. And therefore, we just take it away

27:45.147 --> 27:48.972
from the contract research program. this year, 
give it back next year. And, you know, just this

27:52.813 --> 28:00.283
continual encroachment of in-house versus 
contract research. It's kind of insidious. Now,

28:01.825 --> 28:04.188
by in-house... I mean in-house Navy labs, NOAA 
laboratories, EPA laboratories. I think these

28:12.479 --> 28:19.127
are necessary for carefully applied research and 
